cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and modeling of word definitions. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new model that employs latent variable modeling and soft attention mechanisms. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of distributed vector representations of words. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper proposes a neural network-based model. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper employs soft attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks.
